
[1]amalgamate

   AMAL'GAMATE, v.t.

   1. To mix quicksilver with another metal. Gregory uses amalgamize.

   2. To mix different things, to make a compound; to unite.

         AMAL'GAMATE, v.i. To mix or unite in an amalgam; to blend.
